Description: Sherd of pottery transport amphora, mended from three fragments; inner surface lost; light brown clay with varied inclusions, especially white, but virtually no mica. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 416)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Johnston 2006b / The Delta: From Gamma to Zeta (p.29 Table 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.081)
